The paper also mentions using object proposals and multi-scale sliding windows, which are common techniques in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning, specifically deep learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Additionally, the paper involves integrating local appearance and holistic view, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper also mentions experimental results, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves joint detection and localization, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
